      "side": 1,
      "message": "ubi_ver is the major release version as opposed to a more specific image tag. The base image looks along the lines of \"registry.access.redhat.com/ubi10/ubi:10.2\" or \"registry.access.redhat.com/ubi9/ubi:latest\", where the ubi version is 10 or 9 and the image tag is 10.2 or latest. \n\nMy thought process was that keeping the image tag separate from the major release version might better accommodate future major releases especially since the latest tag can apply to multiple major releases of UBI. If this is irrelevant and the UBI major release and the image tag should be coupled, I will make that change.",
